  "prompt": "What are some examples of fiction written in the future tense?",
  "response": "Future tense is less common in fiction than past or present tense, but it can be found in experimental or speculative works. Here are a few examples:\n\n1. **\"If on a Winter's Night a Traveler\" by Italo Calvino** - The structure and form of this novel play with various tenses, including future tense scenarios.\n2. **\"The Time Machine\" by H.G. Wells** - While primarily in past tense, portions of the narrative speculate on future events and conditions.\n3. **\"Woman on the Edge of Time\" by Marge Piercy** - This novel includes sections that describe a utopian future.\n4. **\"Parable of the Sower\" by Octavia Butler** - Some sections use future tense to project what will happen as the story unfolds.\n5. **\"Cloud Atlas\" by David Mitchell** - Although primarily written in past and present tense, it features future tense in its speculative segments.\n6. **\"Instructions\" by Neil Gaiman** - A short story that often uses future tense to guide the reader through an imaginative journey.\n\nThese examples demonstrate various ways future tense can be used in fiction to create anticipation, speculation, or hypothetical scenarios.",
